The article highlights the importance of caring for America's veterans and their families, caregivers, and survivors. It mentions the signing of the Sergeant First Class Heath Robinson Honoring our Promise to Address Comprehensive Toxics Act of 2022 (PACT Act), which is considered the most significant bill in American history to address veterans' exposure to burn pits and other toxic substances. The law provides more than 5 million veterans with expanded access to healthcare and disability compensation benefits. The President's administration has also taken action to address veteran suicide, advance equity in veterans' services, and expand access to specialized cancer screenings and reproductive health care. The article concludes by mentioning that the Budget proposes to further honor America's commitment to veterans and military families.